T2  - Que risque l'enfant obese?
A1  - Nicolino, Marc
A1  - Villanueva, Cahine
Y1  - 2015//
N2  - The complications of obesity may be observed during childhood. They include multiple and varied anomalies that are found in all major organ systems. These abnormalities occur in the more or less long term. In this context, the question of the impact of early development of obesity on overall health status and mortality is asked. The most frequent comorbidities are described and the different clinical and para-clinical indicators that allow to detect them.
